{"type":"message","id":"a5c4a286","parentId":"9271761a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:09:04.253Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it. Let me read that file.","thinkingSignature":"8eba67ddb669ef0fd13fafd3953368075c451dec070490a53d25821a18254007"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oj83oelj695y_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 110821.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":722,"output":63,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12922,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774364941914}}
{"type":"message","id":"e50f146a","parentId":"a5c4a286","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:09:04.270Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oj83oelj695y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 110821\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what single concrete action I should take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment - comparing next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n3. Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nFrom the CFI_RESULTS.md findings:\r\n- 44.8% have CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI >=0.7 (true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181 - frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\r\n\r\nThe next logical step based on the notes is the \"CFI-weighted compression experiment\" - comparing CFI-weighted vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment that:\r\n1. Takes the frequency-invariant analysis from CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n2. Creates a comparison between frequency-weighted compression vs CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. Tests which method better predicts next-pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's in the research directory and understand the data structure better, then design and implement the experiment.\r\n\r\nSince I need to be concrete and specific, I'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads the frequency invariant data\r\n2. Compares frequency-based weighting vs CFI-based weighting\r\n3. Tests next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me craft a concrete action - creating a CFI-weighted compression experiment script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure metaprogramming noise (CFI=0) while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). The natural next step is to test whether CFI-weighted compression outperforms frequency-based compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-weighted compression for predicting next-pulse content. This tests the core hypothesis that causal persistence (CFI) is more predictive than frequency alone.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression (preserving high-CFI invariants) outperforms frequency-weighted compression for predicting next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Extract frequency invariants from recent pulse history\r\n2. Score each invariant by two methods: frequency weight vs CFI weight\r\n3. Compress each pulse using top-K invariants from each method\r\n4. Measure prediction accuracy: how well compressed content predicts next pulse\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency baseline: ~18.1% mean CFI (from prior analysis)\r\n- CFI-weighted: Should show higher prediction accuracy for high-CFI invariants\r\n- Low-CFI invariants (44.8%) should have near-zero predictive value\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"CFI-weighted vs frequency-weighted compression experiment.\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_dir: str) -> list:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract text invariants from pulse files.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_path = Path(pulse_dir)\r\n    pulses = sorted(pulse_path.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    all_invariants = []\r\n    \r\n    for pulse_file in pulses:\r\n        content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n        # Extract potential invariants (lines appearing in multiple pulses)\r\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in content.split('\\n') if l.strip()]\r\n        all_invariants.extend(lines)\r\n    \r\n    return all_invariants\r\n\r\ndef compute_frequency_weights(invariants: list) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Compute frequency weight for each invariant.\"\"\"\r\n    freq = Counter(invariants)\r\n    total = len(invariants)\r\n    return {inv: count/total for inv, count in freq.items()}\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi(invariant: str, pulse_dir: str) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Compute Cross-Frequency Invariance score.\r\n    CFI = 1 if invariant appears at same frequency in all sessions\r\n    CFI = 0 if invariant appears randomly/never\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    pulse_path = Path(pulse_dir)\r\n    pulses = sorted(pulse_path.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    \r\n    sessions = {}\r\n    for pulse_file in pulses:\r\n        # Extract session ID from filename\r\n        match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})', pulse_file.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            session = match.group(1)\r\n        else:\r\n            session = 'default'\r\n        \r\n        if session not in sessions:\r\n            sessions[session] = set()\r\n        \r\n        content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n        if invariant in content:\r\n            sessions[session].add(pulse_file.stem)\r\n    \r\n    if len(sessions) < 2:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    # Compute coefficient of variation for frequency across sessions\r\n    frequencies = [len(pulses) / len(sessions[session]) if sessions[session] else 0 \r\n                   for session in sessions]\r\n    \r\n    if all(f == frequencies[0] for f in frequencies):\r\n        return 1.0  # Perfect invariance\r\n    elif all(f == 0 for f in frequencies):\r\n        return 0.0  # No invariance\r\n    else:\r\n        # Partial invariance\r\n        variance = sum((f - sum(frequencies)/len(frequencies))**2 for f in frequencies) / len(frequencies)\r\n        std_dev = variance ** 0.5\r\n        mean = sum(frequencies) / len(frequencies)\r\n        cv = std_dev / mean if mean > 0 else float('inf')\r\n        return max(0, 1 - cv\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:08:55\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774364944266}}
